I am a yellow belt at Tae Kwon Do, age 14, and i love martial arts. I'm only doing this because no-one else, who could do a much better job, hasn't.
Martial Arts are arts of combat. Anything. Kung fu, karate, tae kwon do, judo, anything which is a style of fighting. Strictly speaking, brawling, free fight and jeet kune do are martial arts, but they are variable martial arts (no set movements) so they adjust to modern society better than 'pure' martial arts like TKD and kung fu, which stay as created until updated under a new name (ryu/ken/kan) of the original style.